[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Hey everyone, Quen 3TS is a family of texttospech models from Alibaba that can clone voices and create new ones based on text descriptions. It also provides custom voices that we can fine-tune with text. In this video, let\'s see how to'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'use Quen 3TS using the Wong GP tool. Also, if you use my portable builds of the Wong GP tool, you should know that I have added Sage Attention to the latest versions, so you don\'t need to install'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it manually. Now let\'s get started by switching over to the Wonggp tool. Now let\'s choose QN3TS in the model selection option. First we need to change the category from 12.1 to'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'TTS. Then select QN3 1.7B followed by the base 12 hertz model which is the one we use for cloning voices. Quen 3TS supports 10 languages'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'including Chinese, English, French, German, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Portuguese, Russian, and Spanish. If you use any of these languages, selected'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'under the language option, I\'ll be selecting English. Then under the reference voice option, we need to load the audio containing the voice we want to clone. If you want to record your own'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'voice, use the mic button available here. But I will be using an existing audio file. So let\'s click on click to upload. Let\'s choose this audio file and click open. Now let\'s play the audio so'

[01:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you can get an idea of what the voice sounds like. The elephant and the mouse. Oh, how large he is, isn\'t he? And such wonderfully strong legs. See his trunk,'

[01:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'too? Isn\'t it cute? And he is well stuffed. This is really one of the best toys that ever came into our shop. Gerald Dean, don\'t you think so? &gt;&gt; Now that you know what the voice sounds'

[01:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'like, remember that if your audio is too long, you can use the trim option to shorten it. Now, let\'s scroll down. There is an option here for removing background music, but since it isn\'t perfect yet, we\'ll skip it for now.'

[02:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Next, we have the prompts box where we type the text we want the model to speak. I have some text ready in my notepad, so I\'m going to copy one of those lines and paste it directly into the prompts box. There is also an option'

[02:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to provide a transcription of the reference audio. However, in my testing, I found it can introduce unwanted sounds into the output. So, I recommend leaving it blank for better results. Next, we have the max duration option for setting'

[02:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the output length. Right now, it is 30 seconds. So, if you want more length, increase the value. Also, the length depends on the text we wrote in the prompts field. So if we use 30 seconds here but the words are only 10 seconds'

[02:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'long, we will get a 10-second audio. I found the best maximum output length is 20. Above that, you may get possives in the output audio. For right now, I\'m going to use 30. Now let\'s go to the'

[02:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'advanced mode. The seed value I\'m going to use is minus1, which means a random seed will be used for every generation. Then we have the temperature and top K options which can be changed to add'

[03:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'variations to the speech in the output audio. For now I am going to use the default values. Next let\'s go to the MISK tab. Here we can override the default memory profile. If you feel WGP'

[03:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'isn\'t using enough VRAM or the generation is slow, you can select a higher profile. We also have an option for overriding the default attention mode. So let\'s choose SDPA for now. It'

[03:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is slower but it produces better quality output. Now we are ready. Let\'s scroll up, click the generate button and wait for the result. The generation is completed and it was slower. I think it'

